<body>

<div class="header">
  <h1>⚡ JVM Deep Internals — Part 2</h1>
  <p>JMM · Object Layout · Lock Inflation · References · Class Loading · Metaspace · Execution</p>
</div>
<div class="legend">
  <div class="li"><div class="ld" style="background:#1158a7"></div>6 · Java Memory Model</div>
  <div class="li"><div class="ld" style="background:#1a7f37"></div>7 · Object Layout & Locking</div>
  <div class="li"><div class="ld" style="background:#aa5500"></div>8 · Reference Types</div>
  <div class="li"><div class="ld" style="background:#8b4500"></div>9 · Virtual Dispatch & Lambda</div>
  <div class="li"><div class="ld" style="background:#5a189a"></div>10 · String Pool & Special Areas</div>
  <div class="li"><div class="ld" style="background:#1a6b6b"></div>11 · JVM Startup & Tooling</div>
  <div class="li"><div class="ld" style="background:#1a6b9c"></div>12 · Class Loading & Metaspace</div>
  <div class="li"><div class="ld" style="background:#9c1a56"></div>13 · Allocation & Execution</div>
</div>

<div class="main">
<div class="diagram-area">

<div class="stage s6">
  <div class="st">Stage 6 — Java Memory Model (JMM)</div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('jmm-overview')">
      <div class="ctag">JSR-133</div>
      <div class="cl">JMM Overview</div>
      <div class="cd">Defines visibility & ordering rules across threads · Happens-before is the core primitive</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('happens-before')">
      <div class="ctag">ordering</div>
      <div class="cl">Happens-Before (HB)</div>
      <div class="cd">8 rules: unlock→lock · volatile write→read · Thread.start · Thread.join · etc.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('volatile')">
      <div class="ctag">keyword</div>
      <div class="cl">volatile</div>
      <div class="cd">Visibility guarantee · MFENCE barrier · No compound atomicity · Prevents reordering</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('synchronized-jmm')">
      <div class="ctag">monitor</div>
      <div class="cl">synchronized</div>
      <div class="cd">Mutual exclusion + full memory barrier on entry/exit · Establishes HB between unlock and next lock</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('final-jmm')">
      <div class="ctag">safe pub</div>
      <div class="cl">final fields</div>
      <div class="cd">JMM guarantees: after constructor completes, final fields visible to all threads without sync</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('cpu-reorder')">
      <div class="ctag">hardware</div>
      <div class="cl">CPU Reordering & Visibility</div>
      <div class="cd">Store buffers · Invalidation queues · TSO model · Why JMM is needed at all</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="arrow">↓ object lives in heap — what does it look like in memory?</div>

<div class="stage s7">
  <div class="st">Stage 7 — Object Memory Layout & Monitor / Lock Inflation</div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('object-header')">
      <div class="ctag">12-16 bytes</div>
      <div class="cl">Object Header</div>
      <div class="cd">Mark Word (8 bytes) + Klass Pointer (4–8 bytes) + optional array length · Before any fields</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('mark-word')">
      <div class="ctag">64-bit</div>
      <div class="cl">Mark Word Layout</div>
      <div class="cd">Lock bits [2] · GC age [4] · Identity hashcode [31] · Biased thread ID · Forward pointer</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('compressed-oops')">
      <div class="ctag">-XX:+UseCompressedOops</div>
      <div class="cl">Compressed OOPs</div>
      <div class="cd">32-bit object pointers on 64-bit JVM · Heap &lt; 32GB → 4-byte refs · Saves 30–40% memory</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('lock-unlocked')">
      <div class="cl">① Unlocked</div>
      <div class="cd">Mark word stores identity hashcode + GC age. Lock bits = 01</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;font-size:12px;color:var(--sa)">→</div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('lock-biased')">
      <div class="cl">② Biased Lock</div>
      <div class="cd">Thread ID in mark word. No CAS on re-entry. Revoke on contention. Lock bits = 101</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;font-size:12px;color:var(--sa)">→</div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('lock-thin')">
      <div class="cl">③ Thin Lock (Lightweight)</div>
      <div class="cd">CAS swap of stack pointer into mark word. Spin retry. Lock bits = 00</div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;font-size:12px;color:var(--sa)">→</div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('lock-fat')">
      <div class="cl">④ Fat Lock (Inflated)</div>
      <div class="cd">OS mutex (futex). Pointer to ObjectMonitor. Blocking wait queue. Lock bits = 10</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div style="margin-top:6px">
    <div class="lock-flow">
      <div class="ls" style="background:rgba(86,211,100,0.1);color:var(--sa)">No contention → Biased</div>
      <div class="la2">→ first contention →</div>
      <div class="ls" style="background:rgba(86,211,100,0.15);color:var(--sa)">Revoke → Thin Lock</div>
      <div class="la2">→ contention persists →</div>
      <div class="ls" style="background:rgba(255,158,100,0.15);color:var(--pa)">Inflate → Fat Lock</div>
      <div class="la2">→ unlock + no waiters →</div>
      <div class="ls" style="background:rgba(86,211,100,0.1);color:var(--sa)">Deflate possible</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="arrow">↓ objects may be weakly or softly reachable</div>

<div class="stage s8">
  <div class="st">Stage 8 — Reference Types, Finalization &amp; Off-Heap</div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('strong-ref')">
      <div class="ctag">default</div>
      <div class="cl">Strong Reference</div>
      <div class="cd">Normal Java variable reference. Object NEVER GC-d while a strong ref exists. Most common</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('soft-ref')">
      <div class="ctag">SoftReference</div>
      <div class="cl">Soft Reference</div>
      <div class="cd">GC-d only when JVM is low on memory. Ideal for memory-sensitive caches. LRU-like behavior</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('weak-ref')">
      <div class="ctag">WeakReference</div>
      <div class="cl">Weak Reference</div>
      <div class="cd">GC-d at NEXT GC cycle when only weakly reachable. WeakHashMap uses this for auto-eviction</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('phantom-ref')">
      <div class="ctag">PhantomReference</div>
      <div class="cl">Phantom Reference</div>
      <div class="cd">Post-mortem cleanup. get() always returns null. Enqueued AFTER finalization. Cleaner API uses this</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('ref-queue')">
      <div class="ctag">ReferenceQueue</div>
      <div class="cl">ReferenceQueue</div>
      <div class="cd">GC enqueues cleared references here. Your thread polls it to trigger cleanup actions</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('finalize')">
      <div class="ctag">deprecated</div>
      <div class="cl">finalize() &amp; Cleaner</div>
      <div class="cd">finalize(): unpredictable, causes GC resurrection, deprecated Java 9. Cleaner (Java 9+): safe replacement</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('off-heap')">
      <div class="ctag">Unsafe / NIO</div>
      <div class="cl">Off-Heap Memory</div>
      <div class="cd">DirectByteBuffer · unsafe.allocateMemory · Not GC-managed · Freed by Cleaner or unsafe.freeMemory</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="arrow">↓ JIT decides how to dispatch method calls</div>

<div class="stage s9">
  <div class="st">Stage 9 — Virtual Dispatch, invokedynamic &amp; Lambda Internals</div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('vtable')">
      <div class="ctag">invokevirtual</div>
      <div class="cl">vtable (Virtual Method Table)</div>
      <div class="cd">Per-class table of pointers to virtual method implementations · Index fixed at compile time · O(1) dispatch</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('itable')">
      <div class="ctag">invokeinterface</div>
      <div class="cl">itable (Interface Table)</div>
      <div class="cd">Per-class table for interface methods · Slower than vtable (interface index unknown at compile time)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('inline-caches')">
      <div class="ctag">JIT optimization</div>
      <div class="cl">Inline Caches</div>
      <div class="cd">Mono (1 type) → devirtualize fully. Poly (2-3) → type switch. Mega (4+) → vtable lookup. Huge perf gap</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('invokedynamic')">
      <div class="ctag">Java 7+</div>
      <div class="cl">invokedynamic</div>
      <div class="cd">Bootstrap method resolves call site at first invocation. Used for lambdas, string concatenation (+), Groovy/JRuby</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('method-handle')">
      <div class="ctag">java.lang.invoke</div>
      <div class="cl">MethodHandle</div>
      <div class="cd">Low-overhead typed reference to method/field/constructor. JIT-inlineable unlike reflection. Foundation of invokedynamic</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('lambda-internals')">
      <div class="ctag">LambdaMetafactory</div>
      <div class="cl">Lambda / Closure Internals</div>
      <div class="cd">invokedynamic → LambdaMetafactory → generates class at runtime · Captures free variables · No anonymous class overhead on repeated calls</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="arrow">↓ special heap regions &amp; interning</div>

<div class="stage s10">
  <div class="st">Stage 10 — String Pool, Class Data Sharing &amp; Special Heap Areas</div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('string-pool')">
      <div class="ctag">heap (Java 7+)</div>
      <div class="cl">String Pool (Intern Pool)</div>
      <div class="cd">Deduplicates String literals. Lives in heap since Java 7 (was PermGen). intern() manually adds. == works on interned strings</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('cds')">
      <div class="ctag">-Xshare:dump</div>
      <div class="cl">Class Data Sharing (CDS)</div>
      <div class="cd">Pre-processes JDK classes into shared archive (.jsa). Memory-mapped at startup. Reduces startup time &amp; footprint. AppCDS extends to app classes</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('direct-bytebuffer')">
      <div class="ctag">nio</div>
      <div class="cl">Direct ByteBuffer</div>
      <div class="cd">Off-heap native memory buffer. Zero-copy I/O. Freed by Cleaner on GC of the ByteBuffer object (non-deterministic!)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('var-handle')">
      <div class="ctag">Java 9+</div>
      <div class="cl">VarHandle</div>
      <div class="cd">Atomic field access without Unsafe. getAndAdd · compareAndSet · memory fence modes (plain/opaque/acquire/release/volatile)</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="arrow">↓ before main() runs — and after it crashes</div>

<div class="stage s11">
  <div class="st">Stage 11 — JVM Startup Sequence &amp; Observability Tooling</div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('jvm-startup')">
      <div class="ctag">bootstrap order</div>
      <div class="cl">JVM Startup Sequence</div>
      <div class="cd">java → OS loads libjvm.so → Init GC → Init ClassLoaders → Load java.lang.* → Init main thread → Load &amp; init main class → invoke main()</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('jvmti')">
      <div class="ctag">-agentlib</div>
      <div class="cl">JVMTI (JVM Tool Interface)</div>
      <div class="cd">Native agent API. JProfiler, async-profiler, VisualVM, debuggers all use JVMTI. Hooks: class load, method entry/exit, GC events, thread events</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('jfr')">
      <div class="ctag">&lt;1% overhead</div>
      <div class="cl">JFR — Java Flight Recorder</div>
      <div class="cd">Built-in low-overhead continuous event recording. GC, JIT, threads, I/O, allocations. jcmd PID JFR.start / JFR.dump</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('async-profiler')">
      <div class="ctag">JVMTI + perf</div>
      <div class="cl">async-profiler</div>
      <div class="cd">CPU + allocation + wall-clock profiling. Uses JVMTI + Linux perf_events. No safepoint bias (unlike JFR CPU sampling). Flame graphs</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('jstack-jmap')">
      <div class="ctag">jcmd / jstack / jmap</div>
      <div class="cl">JVM Diagnostic Tools</div>
      <div class="cd">jstack: thread dump. jmap: heap dump/histogram. jstat: GC stats live. jcmd: unified diagnostic commands. jps: list JVM processes</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('graalvm')">
      <div class="ctag">native-image</div>
      <div class="cl">GraalVM &amp; AOT Compilation</div>
      <div class="cd">SubstrateVM: ahead-of-time compiles Java to native binary. No JIT warm-up. Tiny memory footprint. No dynamic class loading. Closed-world assumption</div>
    </div>
    <div class="c" onclick="show('virtual-threads')">
      <div class="ctag">Java 21 Loom</div>
      <div class="cl">Virtual Threads</div>
      <div class="cd">M:N threading. JVM schedules onto carrier (OS) threads. Blocking I/O parks virtual thread only. Millions of concurrent threads. No reactive code needed</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="arrow">↓ defining and storing the class metadata</div>

<div class="stage s12">
  <div class="st">Stage 12 — Class Loading & Metaspace Internals</div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="c" onclick="show('class-loader-hierarchy')">
