'finalize':{
  badge:'Stage 8 · Reference Types',bc:'var(--pa)',
  title:'finalize() — Deprecated & Cleaner API',
  def:'finalize() is a method on Object that the JVM calls ONCE on an object before collecting it. Deprecated in Java 9, will be removed. It causes severe problems: unpredictable timing, single-threaded Finalizer queue, GC resurrection risk, and can delay GC by orders of magnitude.',
  points:[
