    'GC delay: objects with finalize() are promoted to a "finalization queue" after GC marks them dead. They cannot be collected until finalize() runs. If Finalizer thread is slow, dead objects pile up in Old Gen → OutOfMemoryError',
    'Resurrection: finalize() can create a new strong reference to "this" — the object becomes live again! It can only be finalized ONCE though. Gross and dangerous',
    'Cleaner (Java 9+): Cleaner.register(Object obj, Runnable action). Action runs when obj is GC-d. No resurrection possible. Cleaner has its own thread. Preferred replacement',
