  tip:'The finalization queue problem: imagine a heavyweight object (database connection, large native buffer) with finalize(). Under heavy allocation, objects die faster than the Finalizer thread can call finalize() → queue grows → more and more dead objects sit in Old Gen → Major GC triggered repeatedly → application grinds to halt. This is why finalize() was deprecated.'
